<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 8:11PM CDT  by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF SOUTHWESTERN SIOUX,
SOUTHWESTERN GRANT AND SOUTHEASTERN ADAMS COUNTIES THROUGH 745 PM
MDT...
At 710 PM MDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over North Lemmon,
or over Lemmon, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts to 55 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Thunder Hawk around 725 PM MDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight MDT for
south central North Dakota.</instruction>
